ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to Chiu Chui-chang, a bureau section chief at the Council of Agriculture, the H7N9 virus in birds shows only weak toxicity. Beijing's 1st H7N9 case might be the result of bird-to-human transmission because it is the season for many migratory birds to pass through the area on the way to their summer breeding grounds in the north, Chiu said. (From Focus Taiwan http://focustaiwan.tw/news/asoc/201304130024.aspx). - Mod.CP]

