[3] Zhejiang - 2 cases
Date: Sat 13 Apr 2013
Source: English News, Xinhua report [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/health/2013-04/13/c_132306312.htm


East China's Zhejiang province reported on Saturday [13 Apr 2013] 2 new cases of H7N9 bird flu infection, bringing the country's total to 48, local heath authorities said.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

******
[4] Jiangsu - 2 cases
Date: 13 Apr 2013
Source: Xinhua Net
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/health/2013-04/13/c_132305963.htm


Two more people in east China's Jiangsu
------------------
Province were confirmed infected with a new strain of bird flu, the provincial health authorities said Saturday [13 Apr 2013].

The number of H7N9 infections in China has been raised to 46 to date [13 Apr 2013], with one reported in Beijing Saturday and all the other 45 in the eastern parts of the country. The 1st known human infections of the deadly virus have claimed the lives of 11 people, according to the National Health and Family Planning Commission.

The 2, a 77-year-old woman from Nanjing and a 72-year-old man from Changshu, are in critical condition and are under emergency treatment at hospitals in Nanjing and Suzhou, the provincial health department said in a statement.

A total of 16 people who have had close contact with the two have not shown signs of flu symptoms.

