[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map for China can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1zaU.]

[As of 6 PM local time in Beijing, the total number of human cases of H7N9 infection is 49, with 11 fatalities reported. Cases have occurred in 3 Provinces -- Anhui, Jiangsu, Zhejiang -- and 2 municipalities -- Shanghai and now Beijing. There are also 2 possible instances of human to human transmission, one involving a single contact and the other involving 2 contacts. Further information on these events are awaited.

For a map of China showing provinces, see http://www.mytripolog.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Map-Of-China-Provinces-and-capital-cities.jpg. - Mod.MPP]
